parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure and Hard Brake Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the braking system can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop in time or at all.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard to press
the brakes fail to slow or stop the vehicle
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes feel spongy
and the vehicle may lurch forward or hesitate before stopping.

symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard to press
the brakes fail to slow or stop the vehicle
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
and the vehicle may lurch forward or hesitate before stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine block heater cord failures can cause fires, resulting in vehicle damage or total loss.

alarm sounds.
